## 🎯 Executive Summary

**OPERATIONAL MANUAL**: Complete step-by-step manual commands guide for executing the comprehensive containerized test suite using SOP v5.1 Cybernetic Goal-Oriented Execution Framework. This manual provides all necessary commands for developers, QA engineers, and DevOps teams to execute enterprise-grade containerized testing.

## 📋 Prerequisites Validation Commands

### **🔍 1. Environment Validation**

```bash
# Verify current working directory
pwd
# Expected output: /home/an/dev/elixir/ash/intelitor-demo

# Check container environment status
if [ -f "/.dockerenv" ] || [ -f "/run/.containerenv" ]; then 
  echo "✅ Running in container environment"
else 
  echo "❌ Not in container - container execution required"
fi

# Verify Podman availability
podman --version
# Expected: podman version 5.4.1+

# Check DevEnv shell status
echo $DEVENV_SHELL
# Should show devenv shell path if active

# Validate PostgreSQL availability
pg_isready -h localhost -p 5433
# Expected: localhost:5433 - accepting connections
```

### **🐳 2. Container Infrastructure Status**

```bash
# List available containers
podman ps -a

# Check container networks
podman network ls | grep intelitor

# Verify container images
podman images | grep intelitor

# Check container health status
podman exec intelitor-demo echo "Container accessible"
```

### **🔧 3. Project Dependencies Validation**

```bash
# Change to project directory
cd /home/an/dev/elixir/ash/intelitor-demo

# Verify Mix environment
mix --version

# Check Elixir version
elixir --version
# Expected: Elixir 1.18+ with Erlang/OTP 27+

# Validate project dependencies
mix deps.check
```

## 🚀 Manual Test Execution Commands

### **📊 Option 1: Complete Comprehensive Test Suite (Recommended)**

```bash
# Execute the complete containerized test framework
elixir scripts/testing/comprehensive_containerized_test_executor.exs

# Alternative with explicit container execution
podman exec -it intelitor-demo elixir scripts/testing/comprehensive_containerized_test_executor.exs
```

### **🧪 Option 2: Individual Test Category Execution**

#### **🔬 A. Unit Test Suite**

```bash
# Execute unit tests with coverage
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover

# Unit tests with parallel execution
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover --max-cases 4

# Unit tests for specific domains
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/support/factories/
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/intelitor/

# Unit tests with detailed output
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover --trace
```

#### **🔗 B. Integration Test Suite**

```bash
# Execute integration tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --only integration

# Database integration tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/integration/database/

# API integration tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/integration/api/

# WebSocket integration tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/integration/realtime/
```

#### **⚡ C. Performance Test Suite**

```bash
# Execute performance tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --only performance

# Load testing with concurrent users
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/performance/ --max-cases 8

# Database performance tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/performance/database/

# Memory and resource usage tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/performance/memory/
```

#### **🎭 D. End-to-End Test Suite**

```bash
# Execute end-to-end tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --only e2e

# Full user workflow tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/e2e/workflows/

# Mobile API end-to-end tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/e2e/mobile_api/

# Admin dashboard end-to-end tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/e2e/admin/
```

#### **🐳 E. Container-Specific Test Suite**

```bash
# Execute container tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --only container

# PHICS hot-reload functionality tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/container/phics/

# Container orchestration tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/container/orchestration/

# Container isolation and security tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/container/isolation/
```

### **🏭 Option 3: SOP v5.1 Multi-Agent Test Execution**

```bash
# Multi-agent coordination with comprehensive testing
ELIXIR_ERL_OPTIONS="+S 16" podman exec intelitor-demo mix claude compilation --compile --strategy smart --supervisor 1 --helpers 4 --workers 6 --dynamic-tokens

# Patient supervisor mode with extended timeouts
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --comprehensive --patient-mode --timeout 3600000

# Maximum parallelization test execution
ELIXIR_ERL_OPTIONS="+S 16" podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover --parallel --max-parallelization
```

## 🔧 Advanced Testing Commands

### **📈 A. Performance Monitoring and Benchmarking**

```bash
# Execute tests with performance monitoring
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover --benchmark --export

# Memory usage monitoring during tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover --memory-monitoring

# Container resource monitoring
podman stats intelitor-demo &
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --comprehensive
killall podman
```

### **🧮 B. Coverage Analysis and Reporting**

```bash
# Generate comprehensive coverage report
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover --html

# Coverage with threshold validation
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover --threshold 95

# Export coverage data for analysis
podman exec intelitor-demo mix coveralls.json
```

### **🔍 C. Test Debugging and Validation**

```bash
# Run tests with verbose output
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --trace --verbose

# Execute specific test files
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test test/specific_test_file.exs

# Run tests with debugging enabled
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --include debug

# Test execution with breakpoint support
podman exec intelitor-demo iex -S mix test
```

## 🛡️ Container-Enforced Execution Commands

### **🚨 A. Mandatory Container Compliance**

```bash
# Force container execution (recommended)
if [ ! -f "/.dockerenv" ] && [ ! -f "/run/.containerenv" ]; then
  echo "🚨 Executing in container for compliance..."
  podman run --rm -it \
    -v "$(pwd):/workspace:z" \
    --network intelitor-demo-network \
    --env CONTAINER_ENFORCEMENT=true \
    --env MIX_ENV=test \
    localhost/intelitor-app-demo:nixos-devenv \
    elixir scripts/testing/comprehensive_containerized_test_executor.exs
fi
```

### **🐳 B. Container Environment Setup**

```bash
# Start container environment
podman-compose up -d

# Verify container readiness
podman exec intelitor-demo mix deps.check
podman exec intelitor-demo mix compile

# Setup test database in container
podman exec intelitor-demo mix ecto.setup
podman exec intelitor-demo mix ash.setup
```

### **🔄 C. Container Cleanup After Testing**

```bash
# Clean test artifacts
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test.clean

# Reset test database
podman exec intelitor-demo mix ecto.reset

# Container log cleanup
podman logs intelitor-demo > test_execution_logs.txt
podman exec intelitor-demo rm -rf _build/test/logs/*
```

## 📊 Test Validation and Reporting Commands

### **📋 A. Test Result Validation**

```bash
# Validate test execution completeness
ls -la comprehensive_test_report_*.json

# Check test coverage results
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover | grep "Coverage:"

# Validate all test categories executed
grep -E "(unit|integration|performance|e2e|container)" comprehensive_test_report_*.json
```

### **📈 B. Enterprise Readiness Validation**

```bash
# Verify zero test failures
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test 2>&1 | grep -E "(failures|errors)" || echo "✅ No test failures"

# Validate test coverage thresholds
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --cover | grep -E "95\.|96\.|97\.|98\.|99\.|100\." || echo "❌ Coverage below 95%"

# Check compilation warnings
podman exec intelitor-demo mix compile --warnings-as-errors 2>&1 | grep "warning" || echo "✅ No compilation warnings"
```

### **🎯 C. Production Readiness Commands**

```bash
# Execute complete production validation suite
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --comprehensive --production-ready

# Security compliance testing
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --only security

# Multi-tenant isolation validation
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --only tenant_isolation

# Performance baseline validation
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --only performance --baseline
```

## 🚨 Emergency and Troubleshooting Commands

### **🔧 A. Test Execution Failures**

```bash
# Debug failing tests
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test --failed --trace

# Reset and retry test execution
podman exec intelitor-demo mix clean
podman exec intelitor-demo mix deps.get
podman exec intelitor-demo mix compile
podman exec intelitor-demo mix test

# Check container health
podman exec intelitor-demo mix app.start
podman exec intelitor-demo echo "Container responsive"
```

### **🏥 B. Container Recovery Commands**

```bash
# Restart container environment
podman restart intelitor-demo

# Rebuild container if needed
podman build -t localhost/intelitor-app-demo:nixos-devenv .

# Force container recreation
podman-compose down
podman-compose up -d --force-recreate
```

### **📋 C. Test Environment Reset**

```bash
# Complete test environment reset
podman exec intelitor-demo mix ecto.drop
podman exec intelitor-demo mix ecto.create
podman exec intelitor-demo mix ecto.migrate
podman exec intelitor-demo mix ash.setup

# Clear all test artifacts
rm -f comprehensive_test_report_*.json
podman exec intelitor-demo rm -rf cover/
```

